comments.message:
I think this comparison might be a concern. For example, let:

1. `pdr->num_children == 1`
2. `child_index == 1`

Substituting into the condition yields:

```
if (1 < 1) {
    continue;
}
```

`1 < 1` evaluates to false and therefore we do not reach the `continue` and instead perform an out-of-bounds access on line 419. This problem generalises to any invocation where `pdr->num_children == child_index` holds. Essentially the inequality used causes an off-by-one error.

The following yields correct behaviour and IMO is a bit easier to understand:

```
if (child_index >= pdr->num_children) {
    continue;
}
```

And with that the test below on line 415 becomes redundant.
